                        <h2 class="title"> Education</h2>
                        <div class="entry">
                            <p><strong>2011 onwards:</strong> PhD research degree in Astronomy, at Leiden Observatory, Leiden University. Supervisor H. Rottgering. Using LOFAR deep fields to study AGN feedback and evolution.</p>
                            <p><strong>2009-2010:</strong> MSc research degree in Astronomy, in the Department of Astronomy, University of Cape Town. <em>“A multiwavelength study of HI galaxies discovered in the Zone of Avoidance”</em>, supervisor R. C. Kraan-Korteweg. A near-infrared follow-up survey of the Parkes deep Zone of Avoidance galaxies for the purpose of using the Tully-Fisher relation to determine redshift-independent distances.</p>
                            <p><strong>2008:</strong> BSc (Hons) in Astrophysics and Space Science at the University of Cape Town. Research component <em>"Galaxies in the Zone of Avoidance: An Infrared Study of HI Detections"</em> (<a href="hons.pdf">thesis</a>), supervisor P.A. Woudt. </p>
                            <p><strong>2005-2007:</strong> BSc in Physics and Astrophysics at the University of Cape Town</p>
                        </div>
